    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="280"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/964½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">6 August, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I would be very much obliged if
                    you would see that the enclosed statement with regard to the Shantung <pb
                        facs="0502" n="456" xml:id="pg_456"/> matter<note n="4" xml:id="d280fn1">For
                        text of this statement, see <ref target="frus1919v01#pg_719">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1919, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 719</ref>.</note> is given to the press
                    and secures as wide publicity as the statement made by Viscount Uchida<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d280fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1919v01#pg_718">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 718</ref>.</note> which, I understand,
                    appears in the American newspapers of this morning, provided, of course, that
                    this form of statement meets with the approbation of your own judgment.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
